  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200&deg;C/ 180&deg;C (fan)/ 400&deg;F/ Gas 6</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>basmati rice</strong> and 350ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml]</span> <strong>water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked, then remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/860.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/860.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/860.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/860.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/860.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle, then peel and finely chop (or grate) the&nbsp;<strong>garlic</strong></p>\r\n<p>Peel the <strong>ginger</strong> (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate)&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Remove the <strong>coconut cream</strong>&nbsp;from the sachet<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> and chop it roughly</p>\r\n<p>Dissolve the <strong>coconut cream</strong> in 400ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[650ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and add the <strong>fish sauce</strong>&nbsp;- this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/860.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/860.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/860.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/860.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/860.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong>&nbsp;vegetable oil&nbsp;</strong>over a high heat&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong> pork strips</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until slightly coloured</p>\r\n<p>Once done, transfer the <strong>pork</strong> to a plate and keep the pan</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/860.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/860.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/860.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/860.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/860.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Trim the <strong>spring onions</strong> and slice each one into three pieces&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Cut the<strong> lime<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/860.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/860.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/860.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/860.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/860.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium heat&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>Thai curry paste</strong>,<strong> garlic</strong>,<strong> ginger</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>spring onion</strong>&nbsp;and <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (Can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 2 min or until fragrant</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>coconut stock</strong> and cook, covered, for 4-6 min or until thickened to a loose curry-like consistency</p>\r\n<p>Squeeze in 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> lime juice</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/860.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/860.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
